relation: Memoria2 - #62 Someone exists as a black hole in Lucas’s memory and heart… All he can do is make sure events don’t repeat themselves, but that’s not much consolation.
Memoria2 - #61 I can curse destiny all I want, but I can’t change anything that happened. Now I just wish that the dark dragon, the being who… changed the world, would let go of me… Just let go…

Memoria2 - #60 I have this dream sometimes… I feel awake, looking out into a surreal and twisted world. My mother, in the distance, always silent, always out of reach. My brother, too close, with words but not himself. I try to forget. Or just accept. And now I can’t even remember their faces… They’re just blurs, not the things I remember. The detail has gone out of them. Red hair, striped shirt, brown hair, red dress, that’s all I truly remember… I don’t know what to cling to anymore.

Memoria2 - #59 Lucas is such a nice guy who hates to see anyone sad or angry. But his inner-self is pretty banged up, his psyche scarred. As he slips off into the world of dreams, you’re about to get a sampling of what torments him…
